  <h3>Professional Growth Portfolio</h3>
  <p>Introduction
Welcome to my professional growth portfolio! I am a senior at Ensign College, pursuing an Information Technology degree with a passion for integrating ethical and spiritual principles into technology solutions. As a follower of Jesus Christ, I strive to embody compassion, integrity, and servant leadership. This portfolio showcases my journey toward becoming an ethical IT leader, highlighting key projects, skills, and reflections that align with my goals of developing inclusive technology, leading impactful teams, and fostering spiritual growth.
Résumé
Education
	Ensign College, Associate of Applied Science in Information Technology, Expected 2025
o	Relevant Coursework: Networking, Ethical IT Practices, Capstone Project
Professional Experience
	IT Intern, Spectrum Internet Services, 2023
o	Assisted in mounting a radio transmitter, cabling, and networking an office complex.
o	Collaborated on device configuration, user testing, and ensured privacy compliance.
	Computer Administrator/Front Desk Technician, AngloGold Ashanti Obuasi Mine, 2021–2022
o	Reduced data loss by 38% through organizational skills and coding for item tracking.
o	Conducted Microsoft Office training, improving report submission efficiency.
Skills
	Technical: Networking, device configuration, coding, UX design
	Leadership: Team collaboration, conflict resolution, project management
	Ethical: Applying the PLUS model for inclusive, transparent IT solutions
My initial S.M.A.R.T. goals focused on ethical decision-making (Goal 1) and leadership of the capstone project (Goal 2). The portfolio reflects strong alignment, with adjustments enhancing its impact:


	Goal 1: Ethical Decision-Making:
	Initial Goal: Develop a framework for ethical IT decisions, applying the ACM Code of Ethics.
	Achievement: The AngloGold dilemma response (reporting misuse, implementing controls) and proactive training program proposal demonstrate integrity. The capstone project’s MFA and encryption align with privacy regulations, such as FERPA.
	Adjustment: Emphasized proactive ethics (training program) to prevent dilemmas, reflecting compassion and patience.
	Goal 2: Capstone Leadership:
	Initial Goal: Lead a team to develop a networked office prototype, prioritizing accessibility.
	Achievement: Delivered a prototype with redundant paths (OSPF), VLANs, and accessibility features (voice navigation, adjustable fonts), embodying servant leadership.
	Adjustment: Enhanced user experience with a simplified dashboard and tooltips, prioritizing non-technical users.
These adjustments strengthened the portfolio’s focus on inclusivity and ethical leadership, aligning with my spiritual principles.
.</p>
