<div id="Projects" class="tabcontent" style="display:none;">
  <h3>My Awesome Projects</h3>
  <p>1.Assisted in mounting a radio transmitter, cabling, and networked an office complex. Collaborated with the team to configure and install network devices, implement features, conducted user testing, and ensured compliance with privacy regulations. 	Reduced data and information loss by 38% through organizational skills and attention to detail. Safeguarded confidential files and information. Improved item tracking by 15% through computer coding and registration. Conducted Microsoft Office suite training for timely report submissions.
2. Networked Office Prototype (Capstone Project)
Project Overview
The capstone project involves leading a team of four to develop a networked office prototype for IT students at Ensign College, designed for research and studying. The prototype features networked computers, secure Wi-Fi, and accessibility enhancements, all built using skills in networking, device configuration, and user-centered design. This project is meaningful to me because it reflects my goal of creating inclusive, ethical technology solutions guided by compassion and integrity.

Refined Project Plan
To address these challenges and ethical concerns, I propose the following refinements:
	Functionality Enhancement: Redundant Network Paths
	Implement a dual-router setup with automatic failover to ensure uninterrupted access during outages. This uses OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) for dynamic routing.
	Impact: Enhances reliability, reflecting patience in ensuring robust solutions.

	User Experience Improvement: Simplified Interface
	Redesign the resource access portal using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create a user-friendly dashboard with clear navigation and tooltips.
	Impact: Improves inclusivity, aligning with compassion by catering to non-technical users.
	Scalability Upgrade: VLAN Configuration
	Implement VLANs (Virtual Local Area Networks) to segment traffic and support up to 50 users, with QoS (Quality of Service) to prioritize critical applications.
	Impact: Ensures future growth, reflecting stewardship of resources.
	Security Enhancement: MFA and Encryption
	Add MFA for admin access and AES-256 encryption for stored data, with user consent forms for data collection.
	Impact: Strengthens privacy, aligning with integrity and regulatory compliance.
	Accessibility Features: Enhanced Inclusivity
	Integrate adjustable font sizes, high-contrast themes, and voice navigation using JavaScript libraries like SpeechSynthesis.
	Impact: Promotes equitable access, embodying compassion for all users.
.</p>
</div>
