  <h3>Spiritual Growth Portfolio</h3>
  <p>Introduction
This Spiritual Progression Portfolio encapsulates my journey of integrating faith and professional growth as an IT student at Ensign College. Rooted in Christlike attributes, integrity, patience, and compassion, my spiritual and professional paths intertwine to form a cohesive identity as an ethical IT leader. This portfolio reflects my growth, aligns with my patriarchal blessing, and outlines actionable goals for continued development as a trusted disciple in my field.
Spiritual Growth Reflection
Throughout this course, my spiritual growth has been shaped by intentional practices and scriptural guidance, deepening my ability to navigate professional challenges with faith. Key reflections include:
	Patriarchal Blessing: Weekly engagement with my patriarchal blessing has anchored my decisions, urging me to live true to my divine potential. It guided my response to the AngloGold Ashanti ethical dilemma, where I prioritized integrity by reporting misuse of admin privileges.
	Scriptures: Psalm 119:105 (“Your word is a lamp for my feet”) illuminated my ethical decision-making, ensuring clarity in complex IT scenarios. Proverbs 3:5-6 fostered patience in troubleshooting, such as resolving network outages methodically. Colossians 3:23-24 transformed my work into an act of service, evident in my capstone project’s focus on accessibility.
	Spiritual Practices: Daily prayer and Sabbath reflection grounded my leadership. Reflecting on team conflicts during the capstone project, I realized that patience allowed me to mediate effectively, fostering collaboration. These practices reinforced my commitment to compassion, as seen in my tech literacy workshop for marginalized communities.
This growth has shaped my professional path by aligning my technical skills with spiritual principles, ensuring my work promotes trust, inclusivity, and societal good.
.</p>
